=3DBBD120224_MONEYSTUFF&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_term=
=3D241202&utm_campaign=3Dmoneystuff>=0A is that it aims to capture 200% of =
the daily returns of MicroStrategy. That =0Aeffectively means that, each da=
y, it rebalances its leverage to remain 2x =0Alevered: If the stock goes up=
, the ETF has more equity, so it needs to borrow =0Amore money to buy more =
stock and remain 2x levered. That=E2=80=99s why =E2=80=9Csome analysts =0As=
ay the funds are contributing to the furious rally in MicroStrategy shares=
=E2=80=9D: =0AThe funds are automatic buyers each time the stock goes up. (=
And sellers each =0Atime it goes down.)=0A=0AWell, technically, they don=E2=
=80=99t buy the stock. They try to own the stock through =0Aswaps: Their ba=
nk counterparties write them swaps giving them 2x the return of =0AMicroStr=
ategy, and the banks generally hedge those swaps by buying the =0Aunderlyin=
g stock. [1]  <> Each day that the stock is up, the ETFs call their =0Abank=
s to ask for more exposure on swap. Increasingly, though, the banks say no:=
=0A=0AThe managers of the MicroStrategy funds say they might be struggling =
to hit =0Athe 2x targets because their prime brokers=E2=80=94firms that pro=
vide securities =0Alending and other services to professional investors=E2=
=80=94have reached the limit of =0Athe swap exposure they are willing to of=
fer.=0A=0ALeveraged ETFs typically achieve their desired result through the=
 use of =0Aswaps, which are widely available for the biggest, most liquid s=
tocks. Swap =0Acontract payments are tied directly to the performance of an=
 underlying asset =0Aand allow a fund to double the daily performance of a =
stock or index with =0Aprecision.=0A=0AMatt Tuttle, who runs the Tuttle Cap=
ital and Rex Shares 2x long MicroStrategy =0Afund, said he can=E2=80=99t ge=
t anywhere close to the amount of swaps he needs for his =0Abooming fund. H=
e says his prime brokers are offering him $20 million to $50 =0Amillion in =
swaps when at one point last week he could have used $1.3 billion.=0A=0ANo =
right of course if you are in the business of automatically buying more =0A=
MicroStrategy with borrowed money as it goes up, (1) you will make a lot of=
 =0Amoney as it goes up, (2) you will keep calling up your banks to ask to =
borrow =0Amore money to buy more and (3) they will eventually say no!=0A=0A=
