e stocks went up a lot, in part because of Hwang=E2=80=99s own buying. So H=
wang had a profit.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way it works is that=
 Hwang would put up, say, $20 of his own money and borrow, say, $80 from ba=
nks to buy $100 worth of stock: The banks might lend him four times his mon=
ey to buy=C2=A0stock. (The actual numbers seem to have been higher.) The st=
ock would then go up =E2=80=94=C2=A0again, in part because he was buying it=
 =E2=80=94=C2=A0and be worth, say, $105. So he=E2=80=99d have $25 of equity=
